node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Business & Entrepreneur on August 20, 2021 tagging @rajpatel.official_. May be an image of text that says 'Raj Patel AA 5 life-changing habits all successful people have (A thread)'.

Photo by Business & Entrepreneur on August 20, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'RajPatel Raj Patel @RajP_Official 1.Set up the right focus triggers. Prepare your mental state to focus on getting work done. For example, for me it would be my morning routine that sets me up to have a productive day. Consistently doing this is key.'.

Photo by Business & Entrepreneur on August 20, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Raj Patel 2. Make sure your physical body is performing at a high level. Get your daily exercise in. Good rule of thumb is never take more than 2 days in a row off. This helps you regulate stress and elevate your mood.'.

Photo by Business & Entrepreneur on August 20, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'RajPatel Raj Patel Official 3. Be in a constant state of improvement. Get 1% better everyday. This is known as Kaizen, a Japanese term meaning, "continuous improvement". Get after your day and crush it'.

Photo by Business & Entrepreneur on August 20, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Raj Patel 4. Excel at every aspect of your life. How you do one thing is how you do everything. You can't expect to be good at one thing you fyou slack off on another thing.'.

Photo by Business & Entrepreneur on August 20, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Raj Patel @RajP_Official 5. Set daily KPls A KPI means "key performance indicator". For example, if your KPI for the day is to have a good workout at the gym and you had a good workout then you met your KPI for the day. This helps you hold yourself accountable.'.

Photo shared by Business & Entrepreneur on August 20, 2021 tagging @rajpatel.official_. May be an image of text that says 'Raj Patel R Drop a 100 in the comments if you read anything valuable in this post.'.
